No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="28FB6564FFDBD6550FF3F7BD16543ED8" pageId="13" pageNumber="704" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="605E36EFFFDBD6550FF3F7BD16543ED8" blockId="13.[1463,2671,1103,2320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">
<emphasis id="5295EAFDFFDBD6550FF3F7BD163A3E6B" bold="true" box="[1465,1813,2129,2162]" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion id="A225F80DFFDBD6550D6AF7BD167A3E6B" box="[1824,1877,2129,2162]" country="Cameroon" name="North" pageId="13" pageNumber="704">Not</collectingRegion>
assessed on The [UCN Red List. The Sandy Long-fingered Bat was recently separated from Schreibers’s Long-fingered Bat (
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFDBD655030DF7951B2B3E83" box="[2375,2564,2169,2202]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="708" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schreibersii">M. schreibersii</taxonomicName>
), which is classified as Near Threatened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
